# 7. ゆっくり進もう

Tsukasa: Aha! It's you guys! Which means you're here to check on Saki?
Ichika: Y-Yes, that's right...
Tsukasa: Great! I'll be in my room planning a new show, so don't mind me and go right upstairs to Saki's room.
Tsukasa: Oh, I've just come up with an idea that'll make my show a huge success! I really am a genius!
Tsukasa: And once it's ready for the stage, you're of course welcome to come see it!
Ichika: Haha... We'll make sure to.
Shiho: Saki's brother hasn't changed at all.
Honami: Shiho, let's keep that to ourselves.
Tsukasa: I also need to thank you for walking Saki home yesterday.
Tsukasa: You're such great friends to her. Thank you for always being there for her.
Honami: Hehe. You're such a caring brother.
Tsukasa: Saki's in her room. She was awake a little while ago, so I'm sure she'll be happy to talk to you.
Ichika: Saki, we're all here to visit you!
Ichika: Saki? Maybe she has nodded off? Saki, it's us.
Ichika: Huh...? She's not here?
Shiho: Maybe she's in the bathroom.
Ichika: Could be. Let's wait for her here.
Honami: I need to use the bathroom too. I'll be right back.
Shiho: I always forget she has this cool ceiling with stars all over it.
Ichika: Hehe. They glow too, so it's probably even prettier when it's dark.
Ichika: That reminds me... Didn't we all help her stick these stars to her ceiling? Tsukasa lent us a hand too.
Shiho: Saki's so short but she insisted on sticking some stars herself. It took so much longer because of that.
Honami: Well, this is strange. Saki wasn't in the bathroom.
Ichika: Huh?
Honami: She hasn't gone downstairs based on what her brother said...
Shiho: Does that mean...? Could she have gone out?
Shiho: Don't tell me she went to the observatory on her own...
Honami: But she wouldn't be able to see anything with this weather...
Ichika: She really wanted to see the stars...
Ichika: I think I know where she might have gone!
Ichika: Honami. Shiho. Come with me!
Saki: My stay at the hospital wasn't easy, but there were some good moments.
Saki: The doctors and the other patients were very kind to me, and taught me how to juggle and stuff.
Saki: But sometimes I felt really lonely. I'd look at the stars to feel better...
Luka: Because it reminded you of the times when you saw them with your friends?
Saki: Yeah.
Miku: Where did Luka go...? I've looked everywhere for her...
Miku: Oh, there she is. She's with...? Saki?
Miku: (Saki looks so sad. Maybe Luka is trying to cheer her up.)
Miku: (I should leave the two of them to talk.)
Saki: Believing that I could stargaze with them again once I got better helped me get through some really awful medical tests.
Saki: But sometimes anxiety would suddenly overwhelm me sometimes...
Saki: How do I describe it...?
Saki: I was scared that I was losing so much...
Luka: What do you mean? Losing so much...?
Saki: The time I have to be with my friends...
Luka: Time...
Saki: I kept thinking, we should be having classes together instead of this.
Saki: Or that I should be having fun on that school trip with them, chatting and staying up late.
Saki: I should've been with them, but the clock was ticking away while I was in the hospital, unable to do anything...
Saki: I felt like it was all being taken away from me.
Saki: I felt the same way even about the time I'd already spent with them...
Saki: I felt... So scared...
Luka: ...
Saki: That's why I'm doing everything I can to make sure every moment matters.
Saki: I decided I won't let the time I should be spending with my friends slip away.
Saki: But it only led to me pushing myself too hard, worrying everyone and...
Saki: I'm... I'm such an really idiot...
Luka: You couldn't help but be anxious...
Saki: Huh?
Luka: You wanted to get back what you lost. That seems perfectly normal.
Luka: You felt that all those things couldn't wait.
Luka: But you don't need to be in such a hurry to make up for that time. It's okay to take it easy.
Saki: Really...?
Luka: That's what I sensed.
Luka: I think your friends would agree too. Wouldn't you? Ichika, Honami, Shiho?
Saki: Huh?
Saki: Whaaat? When did you all get here?!
Shiho: We came to visit you, but you weren't in your room. Ichika correctly guessed you were here.
Shiho: What are you doing out of bed, you dummy?!
Saki: I-I'm so...!
Shiho: No, I'm sorry.
Saki: What?
Shiho: For being so harsh towards you. For saying some really mean things.
Shiho: You getting sick and being cooped up in bed the other time was also my fault since I pressed you to do more than you could handle.
Shiho: And I did it again, despite Luka warning me that you seemed a little out of it.
Shiho: I'm angry at myself for not being a better friend and noticing when something wasn't right. I even said some really mean things to you.
Shiho: I'm really sorry...
Saki: You don't need to apologize! It's all my own...!
Honami: No, it's not your fault, Saki. I didn't realize what was going on with you either. I would've figured it out if I'd only given it some thought.
Honami: I'm sorry, Saki...
Saki: Oh, Hona...
Ichika: Saki...
Ichika: You can take your time. We're going to spend lots of time together.
Ichika: It's like what Luka said. There's no need to hurry.
Ichika: We're not going anywhere. We're always going to be together.
Saki: Ichi...
Saki: Yeah... Yeah...!
Saki: Thank you, everyone...!
